# OpenTelemetry Conventions

When adding or modifying tracing, metrics, logs, or instrumentation:

- Consult the OpenTelemetry docs before writing instrumentation code.
  Use the `context7` MCP tool (or `@Docs` "OpenTelemetry" if MCP is unavailable).
- Prefer the semantic conventions for span/attribute names — do not invent attribute keys.
- Always set up a tracer/meter via the configured provider; never instantiate SDK exporters ad hoc in business logic.
- Verify any API against the docs for the language SDK in use; OTel APIs change across versions.
